status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Optional advanced rules complicate max energy calulations
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Technique Resource
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To use a Technique
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
techniques, x.x.x
\end_layout

\end_inset

, an energy cost must be paid.
 The base conse is 10.
 With each advancement
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Advancement, x.x.x
\end_layout

\end_inset

, the cose increases by 5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Damage Diversion
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Diversion
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except for Direct Damage, all other damage may be absorbed by energy instead
 of health.
 The damage may be split at the defender's disgression.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Exersion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When a character's energy drops to 0, the character is exerting themself.
 All instances that would normally go to energy instead go to health.
 You may choose to pass out at any time when exerting yourself.
 If there are no challenges you are currently participating in; or if there
 are 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Passing Out
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Passing Out
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When you pass out, you may not act in any way until rested or healed.
 It is univerally frowned upon to attack a passed out opponent and only
 the most evil character would spitefully do such an act.
\end_layout

